re%20their%20advice%20for%20retiring%20early%20as%20a%20couple.%3Cp%3EAlan%20and%20Katie%20Donegan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EKatie%20and%20Alan%20Donegan%20retired%20early%20at%20ages%2035%20and%2040.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20couple%20was%20not%20immediately%20on%20the%20same%20page%20about%20pursuing%20financial%20independence.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Donegans%20emphasize%20self-development%20and%20talking%20for%20successful%20relationships%20in%20retirement.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20conversations%20with%20Katie%20and%20Alan%20Donegan%2C%20who%20retired%20at%20the%20ages%20of%2035%20and%2040%2C%20respectively.%20The%20couple%20is%20originally%20from%20the%20UK%20and%20has%20been%20nomadic%20since%202020.%20The%20essay%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlan%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWhen%20I%20was%20growing%20up%20in%20the%20nineties%2C%20my%20dad%20went%20bankrupt%20for%205%20million%20pounds%20and%20gambled%20away%20our%20family%20home.%20The%20years%20we%20spent%20fighting%20in%20court%20to%20keep%20a%20roof%20over%20my%20family's%20head%20taught%20me%20that%20I%20never%20wanted%20to%20be%20financially%20insecure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20adult%2C%20someone%20bought%20me%20a%20self-development%20book%20that%20eventually%20led%20to%20more%20resources%20about%20personal%20finance.%20I%20was%20married%20to%20Katie%20by%20then%2C%20and%20we%20came%20across%20a%20Tony%20Robbins%20book%20about%20index%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKatie%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20It%20was%20the%20first%20time%20we%20learned%20about%20investing%20and%20setting%20an%20early%20retirement%20target.%20It%20all%20sounded%20really%20good%20at%20first%2C%20but%20then%20I%20got%20weird%20about%20it.%20I%20started%20feeling%20a%20sense%20of%20guilt%20and%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20do%20I%20deserve%20this%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spent%20years%20reading%20blogs%20about%20financial%20independence%20(FI)%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%20in%202015%20concluded%20that%20I%20would%20be%20a%20fool%20not%20to%20pursue%20this.%20Alan%20didn't%20need%20all%20that%20time%20%E2%80%94%20he%20understood%20it%20right%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlan%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20years%20that%20Katie%20was%20not%20fully%20on%20board%20were%20quite%20painful.%20Life%20as%20a%20couple%20is%20terrible%20when%20you%20are%20rowing%20in%20opposite%20directions.%20Katie%20would%20say%20she%20wanted%20to%20pursue%20FI%2C%20but%20then%20go%20on%20a%20different%20route%20and%20distract%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20when%20we%20got%20on%20the%20same%20page%20about%20FI%2C%20things%20did%20not%20automatically%20fall%20into%20place.%20Some%20of%20our%20biggest%20disagreements%20were%20over%20purchases.%20Katie%20was%20frugal%20to%20a%20different%20level%2C%20and%20I%20occasionally%20wanted%20to%20buy%20stuff%20that%20I%20thought%20would%20improve%20our%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20one%20incident%20when%20I%20wanted%20to%20buy%20us%20Fitbits%20because%20I%20thought%20they%20would%20inspire%20us%20to%20walk%20more%20and%20track%20our%20heart%20rates.%20Katie%20thought%20it%20was%20an%20unnecessary%20purchase%2C%20and%20it%20led%20to%20a%20huge%20argument%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20a%20store%20in%20Nebraska%20during%20a%20trip%20to%20the%20US.%20My%20thinking%20was%20that%20we're%20worth%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20pounds%2C%20and%20you%20won't%20spend%20150%20bucks%20on%20a%20Fitbit%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKatie%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Since%20we%20retired%20in%202019%2C%20we%20run%20a%20free%2010-week%20course%20on%20FI%20every%20year%20and%20get%20tons%20of%20questions%20from%20couples%20working%20on%20FI.%20Here's%20how%20we%20communicated%20with%20each%20other%20through%20our%20journey%20to%20early%20retirement%20and%20how%20we%20stay%20on%20the%20same%20page%20since%20quitting%20our%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dea37822-b7be-4cee-8b8f-6bcc3a04ee8b%5C%22%3EDon't%20start%20with%20the%20details%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKatie%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20We%20tell%20couples%20not%20to%20start%20thinking%20about%20the%20details%20and%20things%20like%20tracking%20their%20spending%20or%20immediately%20becoming%20frugal.%20Instead%2C%20start%20by%20thinking%20of%20the%20life%20you%20want.%20Rather%20than%20going%20to%20your%20partner%20and%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20to%20cut%20back%20all%20our%20spending%20and%20downsize%20our%20house%2C%26quot%3B%20you%20can%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20vision%20of%20life%20do%20you%20want%20to%20build%20toward%3F%26quot%3B%20And%20then%20think%20about%20what%20you%20need%20to%20do%20financially%20to%20make%20that%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlan%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Find%20common%20ground%20and%20a%20joint%20vision%20%E2%80%94%20like%2C%20would%20it%20not%20be%20cool%20to%20have%20the%20time%20freedom%20to%20walk%20the%20kids%20to%20school%20or%20go%20traveling%3F%2090%25%20of%20the%20FI%20movement%20is%20still%20people%20running%20away%20from%20what%20they%20hate%20and%20not%20imagining%20what%20they%20want%20to%20do%20in%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2231b18e80-ce3b-469a-8957-dce847ecbed6%5C%22%3EWork%20on%20your%20own%20happiness%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlan%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20We%20always%20say%20that%20FI%20is%20not%20a%20magic%20pill%20for%20solving%20all%20your%20problems.%20Once%20you've%20sorted%20the%20money%20aspect%2C%20you%20have%20endless%20time%2C%20which%20can%20actually%20expand%20your%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20when%20you%20get%20articles%20in%20the%20papers%20that%20say%20FI%20didn't%20work%20for%20me.%20What%20happened%20was%20you%20had%20endless%20time%2C%20and%20you%20didn't%20think%20about%20what%20to%20do%20with%20that%20freedom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20important%20thing%20you%20can%20do%20is%20work%20on%20self-development%20and%20confidence%20on%20the%20journey%20to%20FI%20so%20that%20when%20you%20get%20there%2C%20you're%20happy%2C%20confident%2C%20and%20excited.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20on%20yourself%20is%20also%20the%20biggest%20gift%20you%20can%20give%20your%20partner.%20I%20want%20to%20hang%20out%20with%20a%20happy%2C%20confident%20Katie%2C%20but%20I%20can't%20force%20her%20to%20be%20happy%20and%20confident.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c312a28f-3a19-4199-8c1c-8920c173c1bb%5C%22%3ETell%20each%20other%20what%20you%20want%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKatie%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20We%20have%20been%20nomadic%20for%20over%20five%20years%2C%20which%20means%20we%20spend%2024%2F7%20together.%20We%20live%20and%20travel%20together%2C%20we%20run%20our%20projects%20together%2C%20and%20we%20have%20the%20same%20group%20of%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20lives%20almost%20completely%20overlap%2C%20which%20can%20lead%20to%20annoyances%20from%20time%20to%20time.%20We're%20still%20working%20on%20this%20%E2%80%94%20we%20could%20have%20a%20bit%20more%20balance%20and%20time%20apart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlan%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20biggest%20thing%20is%20to%20communicate%20honestly%20about%20what%20you%20feel.%20Katie%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20other%20people%20have%20been%20taught%20to%20always%20keep%20the%20peace%20and%20avoid%20saying%20what%20they%20feel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20we%20keep%20repeating%20the%20same%20message%3A%20You%20have%20to%20say%20what%20you%20want.%20No%20one%20else%20is%20a%20mind%20reader.%20If%20you%20don't%20like%20something%2C%20tell%20me.%20You%20have%20to%20be%20open%20about%20what%20you%20want%20to%20do%20and%20where%20you%20want%20to%20go%2C%20especially%20when%20you%20have%20complete%20time%20freedom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpursuing-finanical-independence-fire-as-a-couple-katie-alan-donegan-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1753056001000%2C%22v